          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. This deletion includes glycine residues within the collagen triple helix domain. Glycine residues within the Gly-Xaa-Yaa repeats of the triple helix domain are required for the structure and stability of fibrillar collagens (PMID: 7695699, 8218237, 19344236). In COL6A3, missense variants at these glycine residues are significantly enriched in individuals with disease (PMID: 15689448, 24038877) compared to the general population (ExAC). This suggests that a deletion of these glycine residues may also be pathogenic. This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with COL6A3-related disease. This variant is an in-frame deletion of the genomic region encompassing exons 16-21 of the COL6A3 gene. It preserves the integrity of the reading frame.</Comment>
